// Inca / Andean gods × 12 — the pantheon of the Tawantinsuyu (1438-1572), the
// pre-Inca Wari and Chavín cultures, and the living Quechua-Aymara religion
// of contemporary Peru, Bolivia, Ecuador, southern Colombia and northern Chile.
// SEO funnel at /gab44/inca-gods (index) + /gab44/inca-gods/{slug}.
//
// First South-American pantheon on gab44. Closes the Americas geographic gap
// alongside the Aztec module — together they cover both major pre-Columbian
// imperial pantheons. Continuously-living religion: Pachamama is still
// actively venerated through the August challa offerings, the Inti Raymi
// is again a state-recognized festival of Peru (since 1944), and the Apu
// mountain-spirits are still invoked in every despacho ceremony from
// Cuzco to La Paz to the Cordillera Real.
//
// Three families × 4 deities, drawn from the canonical Spanish-chronicle
// corpus (Cieza de León 1553, Polo de Ondegardo 1559, Cristóbal de Molina
// 1575, Sarmiento de Gamboa 1572, Garcilaso de la Vega 1609, Bernabé Cobo
// 1653, Guaman Poma de Ayala's 1615 *Nueva Corónica y Buen Gobierno*) plus
// the *Huarochirí Manuscript* (c. 1608, the only surviving native-Andean
// religious text in Quechua, ordered destroyed in the extirpation-of-
// idolatries campaigns but miraculously preserved in the Madrid archive):
//
//   1. Cosmic Sovereigns (Viracocha, Inti, Mama Killa, Pachamama) — the
//      creator who emerged from Lake Titicaca and walked west across the
//      ocean; the Sun-king whose sweat IS gold and who is the literal
//      ancestor of every Sapa Inca; the Moon-mother whose tears are silver;
//      the still-actively-venerated Earth-mother.
//
//   2. Sky, Water & Staple Forces (Illapa, Mama Cocha, Pachacamac, Chasca) —
//      the three-in-one Thunder-god whose trinity the Spanish syncretized
//      with the Christian Trinity; the Sea-mother and Lake Titicaca; the
//      coastal Creator-of-Earth whose pre-Inca oracle-shrine south of Lima
//      was the most-feared on the continent; the Venus-as-dawn-star
//      attendant of the moon.
//
//   3. Living Land, Threshold & Shadow (Apu, Supay, Catequil, Coniraya) —
//      the mountain-spirits invoked in every despacho; the Lord of the
//      underworld of Ukhu Pacha demonized by the Spanish into "Devil"
//      but surviving in folk-Catholicism as the Diablada of Oruro; the
//      twin-thunder-oracle-god of Huamachuco executed by Atahualpa with
//      a hammer-blow to his stone; the trickster-creator-chaser of the
//      Huarochirí Manuscript whose pursuit of Cavillaca produced the
//      island-rocks of Pachacamac.
//
// Source-honest: every page cites the actual Spanish-chronicle source-text
// (Cieza de León's *Crónica del Perú* Part II 1553, Polo de Ondegardo's
// *Errores y supersticiones de los indios* 1559, Cristóbal de Molina's
// *Relación de las fábulas y ritos de los Incas* 1575, Sarmiento's *Historia
// de los Incas* 1572 commissioned by Viceroy Toledo, Garcilaso's *Comentarios
// Reales* 1609, Cobo's *Historia del Nuevo Mundo* 1653, Guaman Poma's *Nueva
// Corónica* 1615, the *Huarochirí Manuscript* c. 1608 collected by Francisco
// de Ávila during the extirpation campaigns, plus modern scholarship: John
// Rowe, R. T. Zuidema, Frank Salomon, Sabine MacCormack, Catherine Allen,
// Gary Urton, Susan Niles, Tom Cummins).
//
// Shadow-honest: each page names the specific extirpation-of-idolatries
// campaigns (1610-1670 led by Francisco de Ávila in Huarochirí, then by
// Pedro de Villagómez); the 1572 execution of Tupac Amaru I and the 1781
// execution of Tupac Amaru II; the systematic Spanish destruction of the
// huacas; the demonization of Supay into the Christian Devil; the
// 1532-1535 Pizarro conquest; the late-20th-c. Sendero Luminoso era; the
// contemporary lithium-and-copper extraction from Pachamama's body in the
// Atacama and Cordillera Real; the political-contestation of Pachamamism
// under Evo Morales (2006-2019) and after; the Disney-Emperor's-New-Groove
// commodification; the cocaine-industry vs sacred-coca-leaf distinction;
// the tourist-shaman-ayahuasca industrial extraction from highland-Andean
// ritual lineages.

